'''Dennis-Yerai Eckert Ayensa''' ({{langx|fa|دنیس یرای اکرت آینسا}}; born 9 January 1997), known as '''Dennis Dargahi''' in Iran<ref name="passport"/><ref name="2026wcsquadlist"/> ({{langx|fa|دنیس درگاهی}}), is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] and [[Midfielder (association football)|midfielder]] for [[Standard Liège]] in the [[Belgian Pro League]].<ref>{{cite news |title=DANKE & SERVUS, DENNIS! MITTELSTÜRMER WECHSELT NACH BELGIEN |url=https://www.fcingolstadt.de/news/11311-danke-servus-dennis-mittelstuermer-wechselt-nach-belgien/ |access-date=20 June 2022 |work=FC Ingolstadt 04 |date=20 June 2022 |language=de}}</ref> Born in Germany and a former [[Germany national youth football team|German youth international]], he represents the [[Iran national football team|Iran national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
After stints at [[Pulheimer SC]], [[1. FC Köln]], and [[Alemannia Aachen]], Eckert joined [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]]'s youth setup in 2013 and made appearances in the [[UEFA Youth League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/vigo/vigo/2017/10/07/gol-tarjeta-presentacion/0003_201710V7P43991.htm |title=Dennis Eckert, el gol como tarjeta de presentación |trans-title=Dennis Eckert, the goal as a presentation card |publisher=[[La Voz de Galicia]] |language=es |date=7 October 2017 |access-date=19 August 2018}}</ref><ref name=citizen/> He made his senior debut with the latter's [[Borussia Mönchengladbach II|reserve team]] on 5 September 2015 in a 2–2 [[Regionalliga]] home draw against [[SSVg Velbert]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Borussia M'gladbach II vs. SSVg Velbert - 5 September 2015 - Soccerway |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/09/05/germany/regionalliga/borussia-monchengladbach-ii/ssvg-velbert-1902/2071723/ |access-date=2024-03-01 |website=int.soccerway.com}}</ref>

===Celta Vigo===
On 4 July 2017, Eckert joined [[Celta de Vigo]] and was initially assigned to [[Celta de Vigo B|the B-team]] in [[Segunda División B]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rccelta.es/index.php/es/victor-pastrana-y-dennis-eckert-nuevas-incorporaciones-del-celta-b |title=Víctor Pastrana y Dennis Eckert, nuevas incorporaciones del Celta B |trans-title=Víctor Pastrana and Dennis Eckert, new additions of Celta B |publisher=Celta Vigo |language=es |date=4 July 2017 |access-date=19 August 2018}}</ref> He made his first-team debut on 18 August of the following year, coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Maxi Gómez]] in a 1–1 [[La Liga]] home draw against [[RCD Espanyol]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/primera-division/2018/08/18/5b7862b6268e3e98068b45ee.html |title=Tablas para ir calentando |trans-title=Draw to start preparing |publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |language=es |date=18 August 2018 |access-date=19 August 2018}}</ref>

====Loan to Excelsior====
On 31 January 2019, Eckert joined [[Eredivisie]] side [[S.B.V. Excelsior|SBV Excelsior]] until June.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rccelta.es/index.php/es/dennis-eckert-cedido-al-sbv-excelsior-de-la-eredivisie |title=Dennis Eckert, cedido al SBV Excelsior de la Eredivisie |trans-title=Dennis Eckert, loaned to Eredivisie's SBV Excelsior |publisher=Celta Vigo |language=es |date=31 January 2019 |accessdate=1 February 2019}}</ref> He scored the game-winning goal on 17 February in a 2–1 comeback win against [[FC Emmen]] for his first top-flight goal.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://eldesmarque.com/vigo/celta/noticias/123637-eckert-anota-el-gol-del-triunfo-del-excelsior |title=Eckert anota el gol del triunfo del Excelsior |date=17 February 2019 |website=ElDesmarque Vigo}}</ref>

===FC Ingolstadt===
On 2 September 2019, [[FC Ingolstadt 04|FC Ingolstadt]] announced the signing of Eckert.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcingolstadt.de/news/9550-eckert-ayensa-kommt-kerschbaumer-geht-fci-personalplanungen-abgeschlossen/ |title=Eckert Ayensa kommt, Kerschbaumer geht: FCI-Personalplanungen abgeschlossen |publisher=FC Ingolstadt 04 |language=German |date=2 September 2019 |access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref> He scored a goal and provided an assist in his debut for the club on 15 September 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fcingolstadt.de/news/9578-niederlage-trotz-schlussoffensive-schanzer-muessen-sich-halle-geschlagen-geben/ |title=Niederlage trotz Schlussoffensive: Schanzer müssen sich Halle geschlagen geben |website=Die Schanzer|date=15 September 2019 }}</ref> Eckert finished [[2019–20 3. Liga|the season]] with 14 goals in 30 league matches, helping Ingolstadt reach the promotion play-offs.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ligainsider.de/dennis-eckert-ayensa_20668/arminia-bielefeld-haben-die-ostwestfalen-eckert-ayensa-im-visier-290850/ |title=Arminia Bielefeld: Haben die Ostwestfalen Eckert Ayensa im Visier? |first=LigaInsider |last=GmbH |date=15 July 2020 |website=www.ligainsider.de}}</ref> Eckert helped Ingolstadt reach the promotion play-offs again the following season, leading Ingolstadt to the [[2021–22 2. Bundesliga|2. Bundesliga]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://bulinews.com/news/8635/osnabr%C3%BCck-score-three-home-but-ingolstadt-take-promotion-playoff |title=Osnabrück score three at home, but Ingolstadt take promotion playoff |website=Bulinews|date=30 May 2021 }}</ref>

===Royale Union Saint-Gilloise===
On 20 June 2022, Eckert signed for Belgian side [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise|Union SG]] ahead of their [[2022–23 Royale Union Saint-Gilloise season|2022–23 season]] after scoring 25 goals and providing 15 assists in 78 league matches for Ingolstadt.<ref>{{cite tweet |number=1540247305168756736 |user=UnionStGilloise |title=🔥 𝑫𝒆𝒏𝒏𝒊𝒔 𝑬𝒄𝒌𝒆𝒓𝒕 𝑨𝒚𝒆𝒏𝒔𝒂 📍 Striker🇩🇪 German📆 25 years🟨🟦 |date=24 June 2022}}</ref><ref name=sw>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/dennis-eckert/330672/ |title=Germany - D. Eckert - Profile with news, career statistics and history - Soccerway}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Union in a pre-season match against [[Feyenoord]] on 16 July 2022.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/641078 |title=Feyenoord Rotterdam vs. Union St.-Gilloise - Football Match Summary - July 16, 2022 - ESPN}}</ref> Eckert made his [[Belgian First Division A|Belgian Pro League]] debut on 23 July 2022 in their opening match against [[Sint-Truidense V.V.|Sint-Truiden]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/641349 |title=Sint-Truidense vs. Union St.-Gilloise - Football Match Summary - July 23, 2022 - ESPN}}</ref> He made his senior [[UEFA]] competition debut on 9 August 2022 in a [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round|2022–23 UEFA Champions League qualification]] match against Scottish side [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2035392/ |title=Rangers-St Gilloise &#124; UEFA Champions League 2022/23}}</ref><ref name=sw/> He scored his first league goal in his following match on 31 August 2022 against [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp]] at the [[Bosuilstadion]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-08-31 |title=Dubbelslag Janssen helpt Van Bommel aan koppositie |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/dubbelslag-janssen-helpt-van-bommel-aan-koppositie |access-date=2024-03-08 |website=Voetbal International |language=nl}}</ref>

The [[2023–24 Royale Union Saint-Gilloise season|following season]], Eckert scored the first goal of the league season in the opening match against [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] on 28 July 2023.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=prznsoccer|number=1685018113488650240|title=⚽️ Dennis Eckert! Dennis beautifully opens the scoring for Royale Union in the 🇧🇪 Belgian Pro League vs. Anderlecht, securing a clean finish and granting les Unionistes a 1-0 league lead. This marks the first goal of the season in the Belgian league.}}</ref> He scored his first senior European competition goal on 24 August 2023 during the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round|2023–24 UEFA Europa League play-off]] match against [[FC Lugano|Lugano]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2039025/ | title=Union SG-Lugano &#124; UEFA Europa League 2023/24 }}</ref> Eckert scored the winning goal on 22 February 2024 against German [[Bundesliga]] side [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] to help lead Union to the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa Conference League knockout phase|UEFA Europa Conference League round of 16]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Eintracht Frankfurt v Union Saint-Gilloise |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68375412 |access-date=2024-03-01 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He scored the winning goal again in the following match on 25 February 2024 during a league game against [[Standard Liège]], keeping his team in first place in the [[2023–24 Belgian Pro League#League table|regular season league table]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Twee goals in vier minuten bezorgen Union de overwinning tegen Standard {{!}} sporza |url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/jupiler-pro-league/2023-2024/regulier/27/union-standard-twee-goals-in-vier-minuten-bezorgen-union-de-overwinning-tegen-standard~1687512428404/ |access-date=2024-03-01 |website=sporza.be |language=nl}}</ref> On 9 May 2024, Eckert won his first senior title when Union won the [[2023–24 Belgian Cup|Belgian Cup]].<ref name="belgiancup">{{Cite web |date=2024-05-10 |title=Machida goal is enough to secure Union first Belgian silverware for 89 years |url=https://www.insideworldfootball.com/2024/05/10/machida-goal-enough-secure-union-first-belgian-silverware-89-years/ |access-date=2024-08-16 |website=Inside World Football |language=en-GB}}</ref>

Eckert began the following [[2024–25 Royale Union Saint-Gilloise season|2024–25 season]] with a win against [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] in the [[2024 Belgian Super Cup]] on 20 July 2024, helping Union win their first [[Belgian Super Cup]] title.<ref name="super-cup">{{Cite web |date=2024-07-21 |title=L'Union s'adjuge la Supercoupe de Belgique: le 15e trophée de son histoire |url=https://www.sudinfo.be/id860174/article/2024-07-21/lunion-sadjuge-la-supercoupe-de-belgique-le-15e-trophee-de-son-histoire |access-date=2024-08-16 |website=sudinfo.be |language=fr}}</ref> He scored his first league goal of the season during their home opener on 2 August 2024 against [[K Beerschot VA|Beerschot]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Union SG 3-1 Beerschot (Aug 2, 2024) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/football/match/_/gameId/703682 |access-date=2024-08-16 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

====Standard Liège (loan)====
On 6 September 2024, Eckert joined fellow Belgian Pro League side [[Standard Liège]] on a [[2024–25 Standard Liège season|season-long]] loan deal with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://standard.be/nl/news/welcome-dennis|trans-title=Dennis ECKERT AYENSA is a Rouche|title=Dennis ECKERT AYENSA is een Rouche|language=Dutch|website=standard.be/nl|date=6 September 2024|accessdate=6 September 2024}}</ref> He scored his first league goal for the club on 20 October 2024 against [[Royal Charleroi S.C.|Charleroi]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.dhnet.be/sports/football/division-1a/standard/2024/10/20/eckert-ayensa-ouvre-son-compteur-mais-rate-un-penalty-oneill-en-mode-diesel-les-notes-des-liegeois-apres-la-victoire-sur-charleroi-2CJ3OSSKW5FFRHBXYA3ULQPFDQ/ | title=Eckert Ayensa ouvre son compteur mais rate un penalty, O'Neill en mode diesel : Les notes des Liégeois après la victoire sur Charleroi }}</ref>

===Standard Liège===
In March 2025 during the [[2024–25 Standard Liège season|2024–25 season]], Standard Liège exercised the purchase option on Eckert, signing him to a contract with the club that begins in July 2025 and runs until 2028.<ref>{{cite web | title=Standard Liege make German strikers loan move from Union St Gilloise permanent | date=26 March 2025 | url=https://sports.yahoo.com/article/standard-liege-german-strikers-loan-113500251.html }}</ref> The following [[2025–26 Belgian Pro League|2025–26 season]], Eckert scored a goal during their home opener on 2 August 2025 against [[F.C.V. Dender E.H.|Dender]] at the [[Stade Maurice Dufrasne]] in [[Liège]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Pro League : Le Standard concède le partage face à Dender dans un match de piètre qualité - RTBF Actus | url=https://www.rtbf.be/article/direct-audio-et-commente-pro-league-standard-dender-les-rouches-mettent-le-pied-sur-le-ballon-0-0-11581686 }}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Eckert has played for the [[Germany national under-19 football team|Germany U19 national team]].<ref name="auto"/>

===Senior===
In March 2026, Eckert received his first call up to the [[Iran national football team|Iran national team]] for friendly matches against [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] and [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]].<ref name="march-2026-iran">{{cite web |url=https://www.didbaniran.ir/بخش-ورزشی-16/277538-قلعه-نویی-نفر-را-به-تیم-ملی-فوتبال-دعوت-کرد-سردار-آزمون-خط-خورد-دنیس-اکرت-دعوت-شد |title=قلعه‌نویی ۳۴ نفر را به تیم ملی فوتبال دعوت کرد/ سردار آزمون خط خورد؛ دنیس اکرت دعوت شد! |publisher=Didban Iran |language=fa |date=20 March 2026 }}</ref><ref>https://www.persianfootball.com/news/2026/03/20/dennis-eckert-ayensa-receives-team-melli-call-up/</ref><ref>https://www.persianfootball.com/news/2026/03/20/iran-squad-for-nigera-and-costa-rica-friendlies-announced/</ref> However, he was unable to make a debut appearance in the March friendly matches due to administrative issues and the absence of [[FIFA]] approval.<ref>https://allnigeriasoccer.com/team-news-former-germany-u19-international-forward-ruled-out-of-iran-v-nigeria-friendly</ref><ref name="passport"/> On 1 June 2026, Eckert was named in Iran's final squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]], without having received his [[FIFA association changes in 2026|FIFA Change of Association]] approval.<ref name="2026wcsquad">https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/ir-iran-squad-named</ref><ref name="2026wcsquadlist">{{cite web |url=https://fdp.fifa.org/assetspublic/ce281/pdf/SquadLists-English.pdf |title=FIFA World Cup 2026: Squad List |publisher=[[FIFA]] |date=June 2, 2026 |access-date=June 2, 2026}}</ref><ref>https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform</ref>

==Outside football==
===Personal life===
Dennis-Yerai Eckert Ayensa was born and raised in [[Bonn]] to a [[Galicia (Spain)|Galician]] mother and a [[Iranians in Germany|German father of Iranian descent]], along with his brother Joel who played [[College association football#Canada|college soccer]] for [[Cape Breton University]].<ref name="auto">{{Cite web |url=https://www.persianfootball.com/news/2018/08/31/dennis-eckert-future-team-melli-call-up/ |title=Dennis Eckert: Future Team Melli call-up? |author=Mir Farhad Ali Khan |date=August 2018 |website=PersianFootball.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://gocapersgo.ca/sports/msoc/2018-19/bios/eckert-ayensa_joel_mu7m | title=Joel Eckert-Ayensa |publisher=Cape Breton Athletics }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vQRETbJ8f-o | title=Beyond the Game Joel Eckert-Ayensa | website=[[YouTube]] | date=13 October 2015 }}</ref> Iranian actress [[Anahita Dargahi]] is his [[aunt]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=همه چیز درباره دنیس اکرات، برادرزاده آناهیتا درگاهی و بازیکن جدید تیم ملی + عکس های دوتایی و همسرش |url=https://www.rokna.net/بخش-شبکه-های-اجتماعی-78/1186552-همه-چیز-درباره-دنیس-اکرات-برادرزاده-آناهیتا-درگاهی-بازیکن-جدید-تیم-ملی-عکس-های-دوتایی-همسرش |date=5 December 2025 |website=rokna.net |language=fa}}</ref> Eckert holds dual [[German nationality law|German]] and [[Spanish nationality law|Spanish citizenship]], and is fluent in [[German language|German]], [[English language|English]], and [[Spanish language|Spanish]], while knowing minimal [[Persian language|Persian]].<ref name="citizen">{{Cite web |date=2018-11-15 |title=Von der Regionalliga in LaLiga: Das Märchen des Dennis Eckert {{!}} Goal.com Deutschland |url=https://www.goal.com/de/meldungen/aus-der-regionalliga-in-spaniens-laliga-das-fussballmaerchen-des-dennis-eckert/151xs27d2hvny18ica1uitywpk |access-date=2024-03-01 |website=www.goal.com |language=de}}</ref><ref name=name2/> He received his [[Iranian nationality law|Iranian citizenship]] by May 2026 and was given the name ''Dennis Dargahi''.<ref name="passport">https://www.persianfootball.com/news/2026/05/13/dennis-eckert-ayensa-receives-iranian-passport-in-build-up-to-the-world-cup/</ref><ref name="2026wcsquadlist"/>

===Sponsorship===
Eckert is outfitted by American sportswear supplier [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Dennis Eckert Ayensa Football Boots |url=https://www.footballbootsdb.com/player/Dennis-Eckert-Ayensa/76693/ |access-date=2024-03-01 |website=Football Boots DB |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://news.sportslogos.net/2023/05/02/belgian-club-touts-new-kit-deal-as-win-for-fans-environment/soccer/ | title=Belgian Club Touts New Kit Deal as Win for Fans, Environment | date=2 May 2023 }}</ref>

